Package gameClient

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Arena
    This class represents a multi Agents Arena which move on a graph - grabs Pokemons and avoid the Zombies.
    CL_Agent
    This class representing an agent, containing helpful information that we "take" from the game server about the agent such as: agent ID agent speed update the agent with new information as speed and so on
    CL_Pokemon
    This class representing a pokemon, containing helpful information that we "take" from the game server about the agent such as: pokemon value (how much he cost for catching) on what edge does it placed in the game graph we has added 2 things to this written class - 2 comparators
    DFS
    This class representing an improved DFS, and returning a list of Integer, each Integer will represent one (and different) component in an directional un-connected graph.
    EdgesWithPok
    this class in a "helper" class, we build this to prevent the agents from walking to the same pokemon.
    Ex2
    this class is merging all classes to one working game, we used the example that supplied to us and did an improvements.
    MyFrame
    This class represents a very simple GUI class to presents the graph of the game, the location of the agents and the pokemons as the game is running.
    myLogin
    This class build the Login screen, user will have to register his ID and the scenario he want to play with.
    SimplePlayer
    Simple player i took from my tutor (yael), it will play the pokemon theme in english, while the game is running
